# Bidding Challenge Recovery: "Total Domination" Strategy

The goal is to recover the performance for the "Bidding Predictions for Construction" competition, rectifying the dataset mismatch and implementing the "Namazani" attack to reach Rank 1 (Score < 0.28).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Dataset Correction**: I found that the local [train_summary.csv](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/construction_bidding/train_summary.csv) was truncated (missing ~800 rows). I have extracted the official Kaggle dataset from the zip file.
> **Feature Strategy**: We are pivoting from the basic [v14](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/construction_bidding/bidding_v14_trinity_fix.py#108-191) to a "Phase 7: Total Domination" approach using granular item intelligence from [raw_train.csv](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/construction_bidding/raw_train.csv).

## Proposed Changes

### Model Training

#### [NEW] [bidding_v15_total_domination.py](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/construction_bidding/bidding_v15_total_domination.py)
1. **Official Data Loading**: Use full 10,621-row [train_summary.csv](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/construction_bidding/train_summary.csv) and 140MB [raw_train.csv](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/construction_bidding/raw_train.csv).
2. **Namazani Features**:
   - Granular item aggregations (pay_item_id count, category uniqueness).
   - Inflation indexing (2018-2025).
   - Temporal lag (days since last bid for contractor).
   - Contractor clustering (KMeans on adjusted bid history).
3. **Robust Ensembling**:
   - 10-fold Stratified GroupKFold (grouped by `job_id`).
   - Blend of XGBoost, LightGBM, CatBoost, and Ridge Regression.
4. **Calibration**: Corrected Isotonic Regression on OOF predictions.

